# BR-001 Gherkin Spec — UI Acceptance Tests (Dashboard, Holdings, Registrars)
# Generated by: Gherkin Spec Agent (Claude)
# Source: Draft test notes 2026-05-09 + BR-001-portfolio-tracking.md
# Covers: /dashboard | /holdings | /registrars
# Stack: FastAPI backend + Next.js frontend (pytest + httpx for API; Playwright for UI)
# Uncle Bob rule: Tests MUST fail before production code is written
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ARCHITECTURAL DECISIONS LOCKED
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Dashboard (/dashboard):
#   Read-only: page never enters edit mode — edit button must not render at all
#   Theme:     persisted via localStorage; survives hard refresh without flash
#   Notifications: overlay/popover pattern; each entry navigates to /settings/notifications
#   Action Items: four alert types —
#     1. Unclaimed dividends  (count + total naira amount)
#     2. Pending registrar document submissions (count)
#     3. Approved claims awaiting payout collection (company name)
#     4. Stale price warning (triggered when last update > 2 days ago)
#   Sector Allocation monthly delta: computed by diffing current NAV snapshot
#     against the snapshot taken on the first day of the current month.
#     Phase 2 dependency — deferred until NAV history is populated.
#   Top Holdings chart: bar chart, two toggle modes:
#     "By Value"  = ranked by current_price × num_shares (default)
#     "By Shares" = ranked by num_shares
#   Recent Transactions: five most recent records, ordered newest first.
#     Columns: date | ticker | type | shares | amount
#
# Holdings (/holdings):
#   Column phase map:
#     curr_value  → Phase 1 (price × shares; shows "—" when price is null)
#     cost_basis  → Phase 1 (stored on holding record)
#     return_%    → Phase 1 (simple return: (curr_value - cost_basis) / cost_basis)
#     div_yield   → Phase 2 (requires dividend records; shows "—" in Phase 1)
#     status      → Phase 1
#     actions     → Phase 1 (edit + delete)
#   Inline editing: clicking Edit on a row expands that row in place.
#     Only one row may be in edit mode at a time.
#     Clicking Edit on a second row exits the first without saving.
#     Cancel discards changes. Save sends PATCH /api/v1/holdings/{id}.
#   Delete: requires confirmation dialog before DELETE request is sent.
#   + Add Holding: Phase 1. Opens a modal — does NOT navigate to a new page.
#     Required fields: company (searchable select), shares,
#     avg purchase price, holding type, status.
#
# Registrars (/registrars):
#   Layout: left panel = registrar list; right panel = selected registrar detail.
#   Linked Companies card: "Link Company" reveals a company select dropdown.
#     Dropdown excludes companies already linked to this registrar.
#     Submit sends POST /api/v1/registrars/{id}/companies/{company_id}.
#   DEFECT (observed 2026-05-09): above POST returns HTTP 405.
#     Root cause: FastAPI router likely missing @router.post decorator or
#     route registered under wrong method. Must be fixed before SC-UI-041 passes.
#   Edit Registrar modal: pre-fills all current fields.
#     Dynamic key-value section: rows can be added ("Add field") and removed.
#     Each row: arbitrary string key + string value.
#     Use case: registrar has 4 phone numbers, 2 emails, custom reference codes.
#     Save sends PATCH /api/v1/registrars/{id} with all fields including dynamic ones.
#   Add Registrar modal: identical fields to Edit modal but empty on open.
#     Save sends POST /api/v1/registrars.
#   Delete Registrar: button sits alongside the Edit button (not in a menu).
#     Requires confirmation dialog. Dialog warns that linked company
#     associations will also be removed. Confirmed delete sends
#     DELETE /api/v1/registrars/{id}.
#
# Defect scenarios are marked [DEFECT] and are expected to FAIL
# until the underlying bug is resolved.
#
# Phase annotations:
#   Phase 1 = current sprint
#   Phase 2 = admin layer (dividends, registrar docs, claims)
#   Phase 4 = multi-portfolio (FR-12, deferred — no spec in this file)
#
