Feature: Dashboard page — read-only consolidation view
  As a portfolio owner
  I want a single consolidated view of my portfolio state
  So that I can understand my net worth, pending actions, and performance at a glance

  Background:
    Given I am authenticated as an admin user
    And I am on the "/dashboard" page

  # ─── Edit button ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Scenario: SC-UI-001 Edit button does not appear on the dashboard
    When the page finishes loading
    Then no edit button is visible anywhere on the page
    And the page renders in read-only mode with no editable fields

  # ─── Theme toggle ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Scenario: SC-UI-002 Theme toggle switches from light mode to dark mode
    Given the current theme is "light"
    When I click the theme icon in the top navigation bar
    Then the page transitions to "dark" mode
    And the theme preference is persisted in localStorage as "dark"
    And refreshing the page preserves the "dark" theme without flash

  Scenario: SC-UI-003 Theme toggle switches from dark mode back to light mode
    Given the current theme is "dark"
    When I click the theme icon in the top navigation bar
    Then the page transitions to "light" mode
    And the theme preference is persisted in localStorage as "light"

  # ─── Notification icon ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Scenario: SC-UI-004 Clicking the notification icon opens a notification popover
    Given at least one notification exists in the system
    When I click the notification bell icon in the top navigation bar
    Then a notification popover appears
    And the popover lists the most recent notifications in reverse chronological order
    And each notification entry shows a short description and a relative timestamp

  Scenario: SC-UI-005 Clicking a notification entry navigates to /settings/notifications
    Given the notification popover is open
    When I click on any individual notification entry
    Then I am navigated to "/settings/notifications"
    And the popover closes

  Scenario: SC-UI-006 Notification popover closes when clicking outside it
    Given the notification popover is open
    When I click anywhere outside the popover
    Then the popover closes
    And I remain on "/dashboard"

  Scenario: SC-UI-007 Notification icon shows no popover when no notifications exist
    Given no notifications exist in the system
    When I click the notification bell icon
    Then a popover appears with an empty state message
    And no notification entries are listed

  # ─── Sector Allocation card ───────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Note: Monthly delta requires two NAV snapshots: one from the first day of
  # the current month and one from today. Phase 2 dependency.

  Scenario: SC-UI-008 Sector Allocation card displays current allocation percentages
    Given active holdings exist across at least two sectors
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Sector Allocation card renders a donut or pie chart
    And each sector is labelled with its name and current percentage of total portfolio value

  Scenario: SC-UI-009 Sector Allocation card displays monthly change delta
    Given a NAV snapshot exists for the first day of the current month
    And a NAV snapshot exists for today with different sector weights
    When the page finishes loading
    Then each sector in the Sector Allocation card shows a monthly change value
    And the change is expressed as a positive or negative percentage point delta
    And sectors that grew show the delta in a success colour
    And sectors that shrank show the delta in a danger colour

  Scenario: SC-UI-010 Sector Allocation card shows empty state when no holdings exist
    Given no active holdings exist
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Sector Allocation card shows an empty state message
    And no chart is rendered

  # ─── Top Holdings card ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Scenario: SC-UI-011 Top Holdings card renders a bar chart by value by default
    Given at least three active holdings exist with different current values
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Top Holdings card displays a horizontal bar chart
    And holdings are ranked from highest to lowest current value
    And the "By Value" toggle button is active by default

  Scenario: SC-UI-012 Top Holdings card switches to ranking by number of shares
    Given the Top Holdings card is displaying "By Value"
    When I click the "By Shares" toggle button
    Then the bar chart re-renders with holdings ranked by number of shares held
    And the "By Shares" toggle button becomes active
    And the "By Value" toggle button becomes inactive

  Scenario: SC-UI-013 Top Holdings card switches back to ranking by value
    Given the Top Holdings card is displaying "By Shares"
    When I click the "By Value" toggle button
    Then the bar chart re-renders with holdings ranked by current portfolio value

  # ─── Recent Transactions card ─────────────────────────────────────────────

  Scenario: SC-UI-014 Recent Transactions card displays the five most recent transactions
    Given more than five transaction records exist
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Recent Transactions card shows exactly five rows
    And each row displays: date, ticker, transaction type, number of shares, and transaction amount
    And rows are ordered with the most recent transaction first

  Scenario: SC-UI-015 Recent Transactions card shows empty state when no transactions exist
    Given no transaction records exist
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Recent Transactions card shows an empty state message
    And no transaction rows are rendered

  Scenario: SC-UI-016 Recent Transactions date column shows current formatted date
    Given a transaction was created today
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the transaction row shows today's date in the date column
    And the date format is consistent across all rows

  # ─── Action Items card ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Action Items surfaces four types of outstanding administrative tasks.
  # Each action type links to the relevant management page.

  Scenario: SC-UI-017 Action Items card displays unclaimed dividend alert with count
    Given one or more dividend records exist with status "unclaimed"
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Action Items card shows an "Unclaimed dividends" entry
    And the entry includes a count of unclaimed dividend records
    And the entry includes the total unclaimed amount in naira

  Scenario: SC-UI-018 Action Items card displays pending registrar document alert
    Given one or more registrar document records exist with status "pending_submission"
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Action Items card shows a "Registrar documents awaiting submission" entry
    And the entry includes a count of outstanding document submissions

  Scenario: SC-UI-019 Action Items card displays approved claim awaiting collection
    Given one or more claim records exist with status "approved"
    And those claims have not been marked as paid
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Action Items card shows a "Claim approved — collect payout" entry
    And the entry includes the name of the company whose claim was approved

  Scenario: SC-UI-020 Action Items card displays stale price warning
    Given the most recent price update for any holding was more than two days ago
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Action Items card shows a "Prices not updated" warning
    And the warning states the number of days since the last price update

  Scenario: SC-UI-021 Action Items card shows empty state when all actions are resolved
    Given no unclaimed dividends exist
    And no registrar documents are pending submission
    And no approved claims are awaiting collection
    And all holdings have been priced within the last two days
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Action Items card shows an "All clear" or equivalent empty state message
    And no alert entries are rendered

  Scenario: SC-UI-022 Clicking an Action Items entry navigates to the relevant page
    Given the Action Items card shows an "Unclaimed dividends" entry
    When I click the "Unclaimed dividends" entry
    Then I am navigated to the dividends management page
    And the dividends list is filtered to show only unclaimed records


