# PAGE: /holdings
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Holdings page shows two tables: Active Portfolio and Claims Portfolio.
# Phase annotations per column:
#   status        → Phase 1 (current)
#   actions       → Phase 1 (current)
#   curr_value    → Phase 1 (computed from price × shares — price may be null)
#   cost_basis    → Phase 1 (stored on holding record)
#   return_%      → Phase 1 (computed: (curr_value - cost_basis) / cost_basis)
#   div_yield     → Phase 2 (requires dividend records)
#
# Edit mode: inline row editing. The row expands in place.
# No separate edit page. Price corrections redirect to /settings/price-entry.
# + Add Holding: Phase 1, opens a modal (not a separate page).
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Feature: Holdings page — portfolio table and inline editing
  As a portfolio owner
  I want to view and manage all my holdings in one place
  So that I can keep my portfolio data accurate

  Background:
    Given I am authenticated as an admin user
    And I am on the "/holdings" page

  # ─── Column rendering by phase ────────────────────────────────────────────

  Scenario: SC-UI-023 Holdings table renders all Phase 1 columns for active holdings
    Given at least one active holding exists with a current price
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the Active Portfolio table is visible
    And each row displays: ticker, company name, shares, current value, cost basis, return %, status, and actions
    And the "div yield" column is either hidden or shows a Phase 2 placeholder

  Scenario: SC-UI-024 Current value column shows null indicator when no price exists
    Given an active holding exists with no current price on record
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the current value cell for that holding shows a dash or "—" indicator
    And the return % cell for that holding also shows "—"

  Scenario: SC-UI-025 Return % is computed as simple return from cost basis
    Given an active holding with current value "54000.00" and cost basis "40000.00"
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the return % cell for that holding shows "+35.00%"

  Scenario: SC-UI-026 Div yield column is not populated in Phase 1
    Given the application is running in Phase 1
    When the page finishes loading
    Then the div yield column shows "—" or a deferred indicator for every holding row
    And no dividend yield values are computed or displayed

  Scenario: SC-UI-027 Claims Portfolio table is displayed separately below Active Portfolio
    Given at least one claim holding exists
    When the page finishes loading
    Then a separate Claims Portfolio section is visible below the Active Portfolio table
    And claim holdings do not appear in the Active Portfolio table
    And claim holdings show "—" for current value, cost basis, and return %

  # ─── Inline row editing ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Scenario: SC-UI-028 Clicking the edit action link puts that row into inline edit mode
    Given at least one active holding exists
    When I click the "Edit" action link for a holding row
    Then that row expands into an inline edit form within the table
    And all other rows remain in read-only display mode
    And the edit form shows editable fields: ticker, company, shares, avg purchase price, status
    And a "Save" button and a "Cancel" button appear within the expanded row

  Scenario: SC-UI-029 Saving an inline edit update persists the changes
    Given a holding row is in inline edit mode
    And I change the number of shares to "150"
    When I click the "Save" button
    Then a PATCH request is sent to "/api/v1/holdings/{id}" with the updated shares
    And the row exits inline edit mode
    And the row now displays "150" in the shares column

  Scenario: SC-UI-030 Cancelling an inline edit discards changes and restores the row
    Given a holding row is in inline edit mode
    And I change the number of shares to "999"
    When I click the "Cancel" button
    Then the row exits inline edit mode
    And the original share count is restored in the display
    And no API request is sent

  Scenario: SC-UI-031 Only one row can be in edit mode at a time
    Given holding row A is in inline edit mode
    When I click the "Edit" action link for holding row B
    Then row A exits edit mode without saving
    And row B enters inline edit mode

  Scenario: SC-UI-032 Clicking the delete action link shows a confirmation prompt
    Given at least one active holding exists
    When I click the "Delete" action link for a holding row
    Then a confirmation dialog appears asking the user to confirm deletion
    And the dialog states which holding will be deleted by ticker and company name

  Scenario: SC-UI-033 Confirming delete removes the holding from the table
    Given a confirmation dialog is open for a holding
    When I click the "Confirm" button in the dialog
    Then a DELETE request is sent to "/api/v1/holdings/{id}"
    And the holding row disappears from the table
    And a success toast notification confirms the deletion

  Scenario: SC-UI-034 Cancelling the delete confirmation leaves the holding unchanged
    Given a confirmation dialog is open for a holding
    When I click the "Cancel" button in the dialog
    Then no DELETE request is sent
    And the holding row remains in the table

  # ─── + Add Holding button ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Scenario: SC-UI-035 Clicking + Add Holding opens an add holding modal
    When I click the "+ Add Holding" button
    Then a modal dialog opens titled "Add Holding" or equivalent
    And the modal contains fields for: company (searchable select), shares, average purchase price, holding type, and status
    And the modal does not navigate away from "/holdings"

  Scenario: SC-UI-036 Submitting the add holding modal with valid data creates a new holding
    Given the Add Holding modal is open
    And I select a company from the company search field
    And I enter "100" for number of shares
    And I enter "380.00" for average purchase price
    And I select "active" for holding type
    When I click the "Save" or "Add" button in the modal
    Then a POST request is sent to "/api/v1/holdings"
    And the modal closes
    And the new holding appears in the Active Portfolio table

  Scenario: SC-UI-037 Add Holding modal shows validation errors for missing required fields
    Given the Add Holding modal is open
    When I click the "Save" button without filling in any fields
    Then validation error messages appear beside each required field
    And no POST request is sent
    And the modal remains open

  Scenario: SC-UI-038 Closing the add holding modal without saving discards the form
    Given the Add Holding modal is open
    And I have partially filled in the form
    When I click the close button or press Escape
    Then the modal closes
    And no POST request is sent
    And no new holding appears in the table


